<inglise> ANNEX II </inglise>
<eesti> II LISA </eesti>
<inglise> GUIDING PRINCIPLES (referred to in the fifth subparagraph of Article 7 (1)) </inglise>
<eesti> JUHTP&Otilde;HIM&Otilde;TTED (artikli 7 l&otilde;ike 1 viiendas l&otilde;igus nimetatud) </eesti>
<inglise> Where a branch applies to join a host Member State's scheme for supplementary cover, the host Member State's scheme will bilaterally establish with the home Member State's scheme appropriate rules and procedures for the payment of compensation to investors at that branch. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui filiaal taotleb vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeemiga liitumist t&auml;iendava kaitse saamiseks, kehtestab vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeem kahepoolselt koos p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi skeemiga asjakohased eeskirjad selle filiaali investoritele h&uuml;vitise maksmiseks ja maksmise korra. </eesti>
<inglise> The following principles will apply both to the drawing up of those procedures and in the framing of the membership conditions applicable to that branch (as referred to in Article 7 (1)): </inglise>
<eesti> Nii selle korra kui ka k&otilde;nealusele filiaalile kohaldatavate liitumistingimuste (nimetatud artikli 7 l&otilde;ikes 1) koostamisel kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmiseid p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the host Member State's scheme will retain full rights to impose its objective and generally applied rules on participating investment firms; it will be able to require the provision of relevant information and be entitled to verify such information with the home Member State's competent authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> a) vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeemile j&auml;&auml;vad t&auml;ielikud &otilde;igused kehtestada osalevate investeerimis&uuml;hingute suhtes oma erapooletuid ja &uuml;ldkohaldatavaid eeskirju; ta v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda asjakohase teabe esitamist ja tal on &otilde;igus kontrollida seda teavet p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devates asutustes; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the host Member State's scheme will meet claims for supplementary compensation after it has been informed by the home Member State's competent authorities of the determination or ruling referred to in Article 2 (2). </inglise>
<eesti> b) vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeem rahuldab t&auml;iendava h&uuml;vitisega seotud n&otilde;uded p&auml;ras seda, kui p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused on talle teatanud emmast-kummast artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud otsusest. </eesti>
<inglise> The host Member State's scheme will retain full rights to verify an investor's entitlement according to its own standards and procedures before paying supplementary compensation; </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeemile j&auml;&auml;vad t&auml;ielikud &otilde;igused kontrollida investori &otilde;igusi oma normide ja korra kohaselt enne t&auml;iendava h&uuml;vitise maksmist; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the host Member State's and the home Member State's schemes will cooperate fully with each other to ensure that investors receive compensation promptly and in the correct amounts. </inglise>
<eesti> c) vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi ja p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi skeemid teevad teineteisega igak&uuml;lgset koost&ouml;&ouml;d tagamaks, et investorid saavad h&uuml;vitist viivitamata ja &otilde;iges summas. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, they will agree on how the existence of a counterclaim which may give rise to set-off under either scheme will affect the compensation paid to the investor by each scheme; </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige lepivad nad kokku, kuidas emma-kumma skeemi raames tasaarvestust p&otilde;hjustada v&otilde;iv vastun&otilde;ue m&otilde;jutab h&uuml;vitist, mida kumbki skeem investorile maksab; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the host Member State's scheme will be entitled to charge branches for supplementary cover on an appropriate basis which takes into account the cover funded by the home Member State's scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> d) vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeemil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda filiaalidelt t&auml;iendava kaitse eest p&otilde;hjendatud tasu, v&otilde;ttes arvesse p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi skeemi rahastatavat tagatist. </eesti>
<inglise> To facilitate charging, the host Member State's scheme will be entitled to assume that its liability will in all circumstances be limited to the excess of the cover it has offered over the cover offered by the home Member State regardless of whether the home Member State actually pays any compensation in respect of claims by investors within the host Member State's territory. </inglise>
<eesti> Tasu sissen&otilde;udmise h&otilde;lbustamiseks on vastuv&otilde;tjaliikmesriigi skeemil &otilde;igus eeldada, et tema vastutus piirdub igal juhul tema pakutava kaitse ja p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi pakutava kaitse vahega, olenemata sellest, kas p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik rahuldab investori n&otilde;uded, mis on esitatud p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi territooriumil. </eesti>
 